\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b subalpina} Gaudin,{\i  Fl. Helv. }{\b 2}: 210 (1828) (incl. {\i V. elisabethae} Klokov, {\i V. monticola} Jordan, {\i V. bielziana} Schur, {\i V. saxatilis} F. W. Schmidt): Perennial or biennial. Stems 20-30(-40) cm, ascending or erect. Leaves and stipules very variable in size and shape, but wider than in ({\b c}). Flowers 2-3·5 cm, yellow, or the upper petals violet. Lateral and lower petals distinctly veined. Spur 5-6 mm, about twice as long as calycine appendages. 2n = 26.{\i  Subalpine meadows and screes, up to }2700 {\i m. Mountains of S. & C. Europe, from N. Spain to the Carpathians and Krym}.
