\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 79. V. aetolica} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  3}({\b 6}): 24 (1859). Perennial. Stems 15-40 cm. Leaves c. 2 cm, ovate to lanceolate, coarsely crenate. Stipules 1-1·5 cm, ciliate, pinnatifid; terminal segment ovate to ovate-lanceolate, subcrenate or entire. Sepals 2-3 mm wide at base, ovate-lanceolate or triangular, often denticulate, ciliate. Flowers 1·5-2 cm, yellow, the upper petals rarely violet. Spur 5-6 mm, straight, slender, c. 1½ times as long as calycine appendages. 2n = 16.{\i  Montane and subalpine meadows. S. & W. parts of Balkan peninsula.} Al Gr Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 80. V. arvensis} Murray,{\i  Prodr. Stirp. Götting.} 73 (1770). Annual up to 40 cm, branched, more or less erect, with an indumentum of short, deflexed hairs. Leaves 2-5 cm, oblong-spathulate, acute or obtuse, crenate. Stipules ½-¾ as long as leaves, coarsely pinnatifid; terminal segment lanceolate, leaf-like. Bracts in upper third of peduncle. Flowers 1-1·5 cm; lower petal cream to yellow; others cream to bluish-violet. Sepals lanceolate, equalling or exceeding corolla. Spur equalling calycine appendages. 2n = 34. {\i Open and cultivated ground. Almost throughout Europe}. All except Az Bl Cr Fa Is Sb.
\par

