\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 85. V. mercurii} Orph. ex Halácsy, {\i Denkschr. Akad. Wiss. Math.-Nat. Kl.} ({\i Wien}){\b  61}: 497 (1894). Sparsely hairy or glabrous annual 2-6(-10) cm. Leaves 0·5-1·5 cm, the lower ovate-orbicular, the upper oblong, almost entire. Stipules usually 3-partite, the terminal segment stalked and leaf-like. Flowers c. 1 cm. Petals yellow, about twice as long as sepals. Spur violet, stout, about equalling the calycine appendages.{\i  S. Greece }({\i Killini Oros}). Gr.
