\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 86. V. demetria} Prolongo ex Boiss.,{\i  Voy. Bot. Midi Esp. }{\b 2}: 73 (1839). Annual, glabrous or with short hairs. Stems 5-15 cm, slender. Lower leaves 1-4 cm, orbicular, subcordate, long-petiolate; the upper 0·5-1·5 cm, broadly ovate to oblong; margins with 2-3 coarse crenations; petiole short. Stipules often nearly as long as leaves, pinnatifid, with short lateral segments at the base, and a large, leaf-like terminal segment. Flowers c. 1 cm. Petals bright yellow, about twice as long as the sepals; upper petals sometimes violet. Spur 2-3 mm, violet, stout, slightly longer than the calycine appendages.{\i  Shady rocks and screes; calcicole. S. W. Spain and W.C. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
